    "DetectedObjectKinematics": {
      "description": "Only position is available, orientation is empty. Note that the shape can be an oriented",
      "raw": "# Only position is available, orientation is empty. Note that the shape can be an oriented\n# bounding box but the direction the object is facing is unknown, in which case\n# orientation should be empty.\nuint8 UNAVAILABLE=0\n\n# The orientation is determined only up to a sign flip. For instance, assume that cars are\n# longer than they are wide, and the perception pipeline can accurately estimate the\n# dimensions of a car. It should set the orientation to coincide with the major axis, with\n# the sign chosen arbitrarily, and use this tag to signify that the orientation could\n# point to the front or the back.\nuint8 SIGN_UNKNOWN=1\n\n# The full orientation is available. Use e.g. for machine-learning models that can\n# differentiate between the front and back of a vehicle.\nuint8 AVAILABLE=2\n\ngeometry_msgs/PoseWithCovariance pose_with_covariance\n\nbool has_position_covariance\nuint8 orientation_availability\n\ngeometry_msgs/TwistWithCovariance twist_with_covariance\n\nbool has_twist\nbool has_twist_covariance\n",
      "fields": [
        {
          "type": "uint8",
          "name": "UNAVAILABLE",
          "comment": "",
          "default": "0",
          "is_constant": true
        },
        {
          "type": "uint8",
          "name": "SIGN_UNKNOWN",
          "comment": "",
          "default": "1",
          "is_constant": true
        },
        {
          "type": "uint8",
          "name": "AVAILABLE",
          "comment": "",
          "default": "2",
          "is_constant": true
        },
        {
          "type": "geometry_msgs/PoseWithCovariance",
